## Checklist Before Creating New Doc

Before creating ANY new .md file:

- [ ] Does this belong in an existing root doc? (README, SETUP, ARCHITECTURE, etc.)
- [ ] If it's a how-to, should it go in `docs/guides/`?
- [ ] If it's historical, should it go in `docs/history/YYYY-MM-DD-name.md`?
- [ ] If it's a technical lesson, should it go in `.cursor/_lessons_learned/`?
- [ ] Am I duplicating existing information?
- [ ] Will I maintain this or will it become stale?

**When in doubt:** Update an existing file instead of creating a new one.

## btl.run Documentation Philosophy

- **Organized hierarchy** - Root (essential), docs/guides/ (how-to), docs/history/ (dated snapshots)
- **Living documents** - Root docs and guides stay current
- **Historical snapshots** - docs/history/ captures major milestones (never updated)
- **Technical lessons** - `.cursor/_lessons_learned/` for debugging patterns
- **One source of truth** - Each topic has ONE authoritative file
- **Dated history** - All historical notes include YYYY-MM-DD in filename
- **No session summaries in root** - Use docs/history/ instead
